Sri Lanka’s Central Bank Lowers 2011 GDP Growth Estimate to 8.3%

-- B y   A n u s h a   O n d a a t j i e   a n d   A s a n t h a   S i r i m a n n e
-- 
2011-10-06T05:51:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-06/sri-lanka-s-central-bank-lowers-2011-gdp-growth-estimate-to-8-3-.html
Sri Lanka ’s economy may grow about
8.3 percent in 2011, Dharma Dheerasinghe, deputy governor of the
island’s central bank, said in  Colombo  today, lowering a
projection of 8.5 percent made earlier this year. The
construction industry will help drive expansion, he said. He
didn’t elaborate on why the central bank cut its forecast.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anusha Ondaatjie in Colombo at 
 anushao@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
